<TITLE> Nasim leaves hospital, to fly to Singapore </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 19 (bdnews24.com) - Former home minister Mohammad Nasim, who was recently freed on bail at LabAid Cardiac Hospital, was discharged Tuesday to seek further treatment in Singapore, a spokesperson said. The ailing Awami League leader left the hospitalwhere he had remained since being released from police guard last Saturday for Zia International Airport at around 8.30 pm, hospital spokesperson Mesbah Azad told bdnews24.com. Nasim's brother-in-law Sajjad Haider told bdnews24.com: "He will leave Dhaka on a Singapore Airlines flight at 11.55 pm." "His younger son Tonmoy Monsur, younger brother Rezaul Karim and younger sister Shirin Akhter will accompany him." Sajjad said the former home minister will be admitted to Mount Elizabeth Hospital on arrival in Singapore. Nasim was arrested on Feb 4, after the promulgation of the state of emergency. A special court on Oct 8 last year sentenced him to 13 years on charges of earning illegal wealth. Nasim was hospitalised in Julne after suffering a stroke in Kashimpur jail. The High Court granted four months' bail on Aug 6, he was released from police guard at the hospital on Aug 16 after being in detention for 18 months and 11 days. bdnews
